A RIDING group for disabled people raised more than £2,400 after a fun day. Riders raise charity cash A RIDING group for disabled people raised more than £2,400 after a fun day.The Riding for the Disabled Association Glasgow Group held their annual Fun Day at Sandyflat in Summerston earlier this month.They hosted pony rides, a treasure hunt, a bake sale and there was a tea bar. Organisers said they raised &pound;2,440. 